 <div class="title" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Integral Cross Sections and Rate Constants</div>
 <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">We plot in 
  <a ref-type="fig" rid="F7" href="#F7">Figure 7</a> the total ICS at 
  <span class="italic">v</span>
  <sub>0</sub> = 0 and 1, with 
  <span class="italic">J</span> ≤ 150 to obtain convergent results up to 3 eV, noting that the convergent requirements change markedly with 
  <span class="italic">E</span>
  <sub>coll</sub> and 
  <span class="italic">J</span>. To minimize the computational effort, the total number of partial waves was therefore shared in different groups, and different values of 
  <span class="italic">K</span>
  <sub>max</sub> and 
  <span class="italic">kstep</span> were employed in each group, as shown in 
  <a rid="T2" ref-type="table" href="#T2">Table 2</a>.
 </p>
